# Apex Dashboard — Django Edition (v0.17.1)

Django 6.0 + Tailwind v4 + Alpine.js + HTMX + Channels (ASGI/Daphne). 27 apps, 1034+ unit tests, multi-tenant orgs, REST API via Django Ninja, realtime via WebSockets. Python 3.12–3.14, deps via `uv`.

For the full reference (architecture, datatable system, API, realtime, recipes), read [CLAUDE.md](mdc:CLAUDE.md). The rules below are the load-bearing ones — apply them by default.

## Hard rules

- **Generic CBVs only** for non-API views. Function views reserved for Ninja API and chart JSON.
- **`TableView` for list views** ([apps/core/tables/views.py:37](mdc:apps/core/tables/views.py)). Subclass it, not `ListView` — you get sort/filter/paginate/export/bulk/column-vis/saved-views for free. Reference: [apps/customers/views.py](mdc:apps/customers/views.py).
- **Mixin order**: `BreadcrumbsMixin, LoginRequiredMixin, EmailVerifiedRequiredMixin, [StaffRequiredMixin,] [OrgRequiredMixin, OrgScopedMixin,] [HasRoleMixin,] [PasswordConfirmationRequiredMixin,] <GenericView>`.
- **Custom User model.** `from apps.accounts.models import User` or `get_user_model()`. Never `django.contrib.auth.models.User`.
- **`Customer` ≠ `User`.** User is internal team; Customer is external. FK accordingly — don't mix.
- **URL namespacing.** Each `urls.py` sets `app_name = "<app>"`. Reverse as `app:name` (`customers:list`, `invoices:detail`).
- **Org scoping is opt-in.** `OrganizationMiddleware` sets `request.organization` post-auth but doesn't filter queries. Combine `OrgRequiredMixin + OrgScopedMixin` per view that needs scoping.
- **Realtime fire-and-forget.** Use [apps/realtime/dispatch.py](mdc:apps/realtime/dispatch.py) `push_notification(user_id, payload)` / `push_unread_count(user_id, count)`. No-ops if no channel layer — call freely.
- **Notifications go through `notify()`**, not `Notification.objects.create()`. `apps.notifications.dispatch.notify(user, category, title, body, url, **meta)` creates the row AND fans out via Channels. Categories: `system | billing | mention | comment | security`.
- **API cursor pagination.** `?cursor=<id>&limit=N` (max 100). Never `?page=`.
- **Webhook signing.** HMAC-SHA256 over canonical JSON body (`serialize_event_payload(event, data)`) in header `X-Apex-Signature`.
- **Soft-delete defaults** for `Customer`, `Project`, `File`. Use `<Model>.all_objects` for unfiltered access. Don't change `Meta.base_manager_name = "all_objects"`.
- **Forms apply per-app `BASE_INPUT`** in `__init__`. Each app duplicates the string intentionally — don't consolidate.
- **Tailwind v4, no config file.** Tokens in [static_src/css/input.css](mdc:static_src/css/input.css) under `@theme inline` and `:root`/`.dark`. Rebuild: `npm run build`.
- **Translations**: `gettext_lazy` on nav/forms. `str()` before JSON or test assertions.
- **CDN scripts have SRI hashes** in [templates/base.html](mdc:templates/base.html). Regenerate `integrity=` when bumping versions.
- **Admin theme**: when registering a new admin, import from [apex/admin/](mdc:apex/admin/) — `from apex.admin import ModelAdmin, TabularInline, StackedInline`. Set `show_in_dashboard = True` + `apex_icon = "<lucide-name>"` to surface a stat card on `/admin/`.

## Mixin catalog (file paths to import from)

- `BreadcrumbsMixin` — `apps.core.breadcrumbs`
- `EmailVerifiedRequiredMixin`, `PasswordConfirmationRequiredMixin` — `apps.accounts.mixins`
- `StaffRequiredMixin` — `apps.accounts.views` (defined at line 60 there, exported by convention)
- `OrgRequiredMixin`, `HasRoleMixin`, `OrgScopedMixin` — `apps.organizations.mixins`
- `TableView` (and `TableConfig`, `Column`, `Filter`, `BulkAction`) — `apps.core.tables`

## Anti-patterns

- Don't edit `static/css/app.css` — gitignored, regenerated by Tailwind.
- Don't hand-edit sidebar templates — append to `NAV_ITEMS` in [apps/core/navigation.py](mdc:apps/core/navigation.py). Register icons in `ICONS` ([apps/core/templatetags/apex.py](mdc:apps/core/templatetags/apex.py)).
- Don't write a plain `ListView` for a list page — use `TableView`.
- Don't add jQuery, Bootstrap, or icon-font libraries.
- Don't `from django.contrib.auth.models import User`.
- Don't FK to `User` for external people — use `Customer`.
- Don't assume queries are org-scoped — apply `OrgScopedMixin` explicitly.
- Don't paginate the API with `?page=` — cursor only.
- Don't `Notification.objects.create()` directly — use `notify()`.
- Don't downgrade to WSGI — Channels needs ASGI/Daphne.
- Don't JSON-serialize `gettext_lazy` proxies — coerce with `str()`.
- Don't bypass `KeyAuth` for API endpoints (if you want public, write a Django view, not a Ninja endpoint).
- Don't import `admin.ModelAdmin` for a new admin — use [apex.admin.ModelAdmin](mdc:apex/admin/base.py) so the theme's `show_in_dashboard` / `apex_icon` hooks are available.
- Don't duplicate Django admin block names in [templates/admin/base.html](mdc:templates/admin/base.html) — Django errors even on `{% if %}`-mutually-exclusive duplicates.

## Recipe: new CRUD module backed by `TableView`

1. `apps/widgets/{models,forms,views,urls}.py` — model, form (applies `BASE_INPUT`), `TableView` subclass with `WIDGETS_TABLE = TableConfig(...)`, `app_name = "widgets"` with five paths.
2. `apex/settings/base.py` — add to `INSTALLED_APPS`.
3. `apex/urls.py` — `include("apps.widgets.urls")`.
4. `apps/core/navigation.py` — append `NavItem(...)` to the right group constant. Register the icon in `ICONS` if it's new.
5. `templates/widgets/widget_{list,detail,form}.html` extending `layouts/dashboard.html`. List template just renders the shared table partial.
6. `apps/widgets/tests/factories.py` (factory-boy); wire into `seed_demo` if you want demo rows.
7. `uv run python manage.py makemigrations widgets && migrate`.

## Recipe: opt a model into org scoping

1. Add nullable `organization = ForeignKey(Organization, null=True, blank=True, on_delete=models.CASCADE)`. Migrate.
2. Backfill via data migration.
3. List/detail views: append `OrgRequiredMixin, OrgScopedMixin` to bases (default `org_field = "organization"`).
4. Create views: in `form_valid`, set `form.instance.organization = self.request.organization`.

## Recipe: new API endpoint

1. `apps/<feature>/api.py` — `router = Router()`, define `ninja.Schema` types, use cursor pagination from [apps/api/pagination.py](mdc:apps/api/pagination.py).
2. [apps/api/api.py](mdc:apps/api/api.py) — `api.add_router("/<feature>/", "apps.<feature>.api.router")`.
3. Auth is automatic (KeyAuth at parent level). Access user as `request.auth_user`.

## Commands

```bash
uv sync --all-groups
npm install && npm run build
uv run python manage.py migrate
uv run python manage.py seed_demo      # demo / ApexShowcase!2026
uv run python manage.py runserver
uv run pytest                          # 1034 unit tests, e2e excluded
uv run pytest -m e2e                   # Playwright Chromium
uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format .
```
